      "message": "Sounds good. Yeah, the difficult-to-review tidal wave of diffs makes the all-permutations thing not sound real pleasant.\n\nAnd I didn\u0027t suggest this earlier, because it\u0027s probably going to be even more difficult to review, but we *could* do SkSL -\u003e SPIRV (via disassembled spirv). I don\u0027t know that it\u0027s going to be real helpful, though.\n\nI\u0027m still noodling on what output format we might support for runtime-effect tests. Currently those get parsed to IR, then converted to either byte-code (which I guess we could dump?), or to \"pipeline stage args\", which is basically a string with format specifiers in it. It\u0027s functionally an SkSL -\u003e SkSL round-trip. Nothing to worry about today, we\u0027ll get there.",
